					</bean>
					<bean class="lt.walrus.model.Slide">
						<property name="title" value="The name" />

						<property name="body" value="&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Why on Earth would the Engineer call a content management system   &quot;Walrus&quot;? The walrus is a rare, funny and friendly animal. A stuffed   walrus lives at the Engineer's office. It keeps the Engineer company   when things are tough and rolls on the floor laughing heartily when   things are good. The Engineer thought it would be a quirky name for a   new system that she has developed.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;" />
